ZCZC GE27
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE AT 232300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING A LARGE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 986 IS
EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER THE SERN NORWEGIAN BASIN WITH A
RIDGE EXTENDING E TOWARDS BISCAY AND N TO THE W OF THE
BRITISH ISLES. THROUGH THE PERIOD THE LOW IS EXP TO DRIFT
E INTO SCANDINAVIA AND FILL WITH A NEW LOW DEVELOPING S
OF ICELAND THIS TRACKING SE THROUGH MONDAY CLOSE TO NERN
SCOTLAND THEN INTO DENMARK AND N GERMANY BY TUESDAY.
THIS NEW LOW WILL DEEPEN FOR A TIME 990 AS IT TRACKS
ACROSS THE N SEA BEFORE BEGINNING TO FILL LATER TUESDAY.
MEANWHILE THE RIDGE EXTENDING FURTHER ACROSS BISCAY FOR A
TIME SUNDAY AND MONDAY BEFORE DECLINING AGAIN. STRG
WINDS ACROSS CULLERCOATS SATURDAY EVENING WITH
WIDESPREAD GALES IN THE N PERHAPS LOC SEV GALE IN
PLACES. THESE WINDS PERSISTING INTO SUNDAY BEFORE EASING
LATER IN THE DAY. HOWEVER FURTHER STRG TO GALE FORCE
WINDS DEVELOP ACROSS THE AREA THROUGH MONDAY THESE
CONTINUING ON TUESDAY
